
[1]indissoluble

   INDIS'SOLUBLE, a. [L. indissolubilis; in and dissolubilis, from
   dissolvo; dis and solvo,to loosen.]

   1. Not capable of being dissolved, melted or liquefied, as by heat or
   water. Few substances are absolutely indissoluble by heat; many are
   indissoluble in water.

   2. That cannot be broken or rightfully violated; perpetually binding or
   obligatory; as an indissoluble league or covenant. The marriage
   covenant is indissoluble, except in certain specified cases.

   3. Not to be broken; firm; stable; as indissoluble friendship;
   indissoluble bands of love.
